    "narrative": "For the LawDog squad on this April 23rd slate, **Tyler Freeman** (71.80) stands as our clear priority play. His matchup against Matt Waldron is the most favorable on the board; the high xERA of the opposing starter, combined with a significant park-factor boost, makes **Tyler Freeman** a must-start in the OF3 slot. **Geraldo Perdomo** (65.92) and **Gavin Sheets** (63.36) also provide high-floor production. **Geraldo Perdomo** capitalizes on a strong SP skill matchup against Davis Martin, while **Gavin Sheets** benefits from an elite 14% park boost and favorable platoon dynamics that elevate his efficiency well above his raw base projection.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today involves balancing the heavy volume of hitters facing Tyler Glasnow. While **Matt Chapman** (57.17) and **Jung Hoo Lee** (51.45) cleared the marginal hurdle thanks to Glasnow\u2019s slow delivery\u2014which provides a subtle advantage for our aggressive base-stealing targets\u2014**Drew Gilbert** (43.24) nearly fell to the bench. **Drew Gilbert** was ultimately saved by his platoon advantage and the stolen base upside inherent in the matchup, despite his low-leverage spot in the lineup. Conversely, **Bryson Stott** (60.16) rewarded our patience, overcoming a tough SP matchup against Edward Cabrera by leveraging an 8th-inning wind-out factor and a strong platoon split to anchor the UTIL slot. As we await final lineups, keep a close eye on **Will Smith** (46.48); while he remains in the starting C1 role, the combination of a tough outing against Logan Webb and lingering questions regarding the batting order makes him our most volatile asset today.",
